(139, 'pages', 'body', 6, 'en', '<p>Judges</p>\n<p>Judges and their status</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Judges are persons authorized by law to administer justice.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>All judges of the Republic of Azerbaijan (chairmen, deputy chairmen, chairmen of boards and judges) have the same status, rights and responsibilities when considering cases and differ from each other only in terms of appointment, powers and terms of office. Every judge (except for a special opinion or a judge who voted against such a decision) shall be equally responsible for all other collegial court decisions, except for the decisions made by the Plenum of the Supreme Court of the Republic of Azerbaijan.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can get information about judges from the single portal of the Judicial system of the Republic of Azerbaijan. Click here.</p>', '2022-01-17 04:48:03', '2022-01-17 04:48:03'),
